data.title: Let Everything by Meredith Andrews
data.meta_description: Original Master MultiTracks, Charts, Patches, and instrument parts for rehearsal. View all products & resources available for "Let Everything" by Meredith Andrews
data.text:
Verse 1

We enter Your presence

Through the gates of praise

We’re ready for Heaven

To fall on Your children

In a mighty way

Verse 2

We’re bringing our worship

As an offering

Holy and pleasing

Hear Your people singing

Out to You

Chorus

Great is the Lord

Worthy of praise

The Lion of Judah

The Ancient of Days

Let everything that has breath

Praise the Lord

The One who remains

Faithful and true

The Lamb who was slain

To make all things new

Let everything that has breath

Praise the Lord

Verse 3

So let our intentions

Be pure in Your sight

Our hearts undivided

A Church and a Bride

That is wholly Yours

Chorus

Great is the Lord

Worthy of praise

The Lion of Judah

The Ancient of Days

Let everything that has breath

Praise the Lord

The One who remains

Faithful and true

The Lamb who was slain

To make all things new

Let everything that has breath

Praise the Lord

Bridge

To the God who is worthy

Be honor and glory

No One’s more deserving

Of all praise

To the King who’s returning

Be honor and glory

No one’s more deserving

Of all praise

Chorus

Great is the Lord

Worthy of praise

The Lion of Judah

The Ancient of Days

Let everything that has breath

Praise the Lord

The One who remains

Faithful and true

The Lamb who was slain

To make all things new

Let everything that has breath

Praise the Lord
